<div class="project">
  <h2>Esquimalt Graving Dock Billing Application</h2>

  <p>
    The billing application was developed as an evolvution from a legacy system
    that was built in MS Access.  We wrote scripts to migrate the data into a
    freshly redesigned database schema that we developed in Microsoft SQL 
    Server 2000.  The new schema addressed a lot of data integrity and 
    performance issues concerns.
  </p>

  <p>
    We then started developing a web based interface for the administrative 
    clerks at the dock to use to manage the existing data, enter new data, and
    generate invoices for their clients.
  </p>

  <p>
    We wrote our own object-relational mapping framework loosely based on the
    ActiveRecord design pattern and called it Supermodel.  We also came up with
    our own object-oriented MVC framework for ColdFusion complete with a base
    controller object and various view helpers for generating form controls
    to interact with our dynamic data models.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our new system has been in use for over a year now and the legacy Access 
    system will be phased out by April 2009.  We are currently implementing
    some more feature enhancements to finalize the system for production use.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="project">
  <h2>Human Resources Staffing Application</h2>

  <p>
    The staffing application is used by the human resources staff members in
    our region to keep track of all the regional staffing processes that are
    planned for the current fiscal year.
  </p>

  <p>
    The application supports three levels of access.  A limited read-only view
    for employees to see what staffing is going on in the region, a full
    read-only view for managers to see the status of the staffing processes,
    and an administrative level for HR staff to manage the data.
  </p>

  <p>
    The staffing application was the first project that we tied to our common 
    login database which is now used by all projects in our region.  It is an
    authentication framework that reads user accounts and details from the
    corporate LDAP exchange server, pulls them into our local database, and
    then allows all our employees to use their email credentials to log into
    any of our applications and gain various levels access.
  </p>

  <p>
    The app also provides various graphical reports to illustrate the overall
    status of staffing in our region.
  </p>
</div>

