<div>
  <h2>Human Resources Competency Application</h2>

  <p>
    The competency application is an electronic resource for employees to find 
    information about what skills and competencies are required for the various
    jobs within government.
  </p>

  <p>
  Managers and Human Resource staff work in conjunction to develop job 
  profiles, competency profiles, and learning profiles for each of the jobs
  that are planned to be staffed.  These profiles provide an overall description
  of the job and what skills are required to perform it adequately.
  </p>

  <p>
    A competency dictionary is included to ennumerate all the various qualities
    and levels of the various job competencies.  The objective is to provide
    a standardized set of criteria for determining whether an applicant is 
    suited to a particular job.
  </p>

  <p>
    For each of the competencies, human resources development specialists can
    attach various resources that employees can turn to in order to build up
    that particular competency.  All the learning resources for all the job
    competencies listed in the job's competency profile are then collected
    automatically and presented in a cohesive learning profile that the
    employee can browse to get an idea of what resources are available to them.
  </p>
</div>

<div>
  <h2>Web Directory Listing Service</h2>

  <p>
  The WebDLS application is used by government staff to develop the BluePages
  listings for local phonebooks.  Various books are tracked in the system and
  users of the system are each responsible for creating a set of listings.
  Some listings are specific to a particular book or region while others can be
  shared across multiple books.
  </p>

  <p>
    The system supports various levels of access so that once a listing is 
    created it can be approved by a manager.  Certain users have administrative
    rights so they can approve or lock listings or lock down an entire book
    when it is ready for publication.
  </p>

  <p>
    The system has precise rules for managing the indentation and wording of
    the listings and allows users to choose from a collection of standard 
    phrases to ensure consistency across listings and books.
  </p>

  <p>
    As a book develops, the listings can be viewed in a nearly photorealistic
    preview mode that mimics the look of an actual printed BluePages book.
    The listings can also be exported into a word document format that is
    accepted by the printers.
  </p>
</div>



